<HEADLINE> Canada Donates Medicines To Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 2 (Xinhua)-- Canada today donated medicines
worth about two million US Dollars to zambia to support its
health reform program.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the hand-over ceremony here, Zambian Deputy Health
Minister Katele Kalumba said Zambia was facing great challenges
in implementing its health reforms.
</P>
<P>
Kalumba said Zambia's national drug policy should be aimed at
ensuring an adequate supply of safe, efficacious drugs of
acceptable quality to all citizens.
</P>
<P>
The government had made tremendous improvement in medical
service and health care, he said, adding that major hospitals in
the country had been rehabilitated, provision of ambulances, drug
supply and laboratory improved.
</P>
<P>
Canadian High Commissioner to Zambia Mary Mosser said her
government was commited to assist in improving Zambia's health
reform program.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian government has been restructuring the health
sector in recent years with an aim to provide the quality medical
service to the people. enditem

