<HEADLINE> Nigeria,India Tied In Film Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian Film Corporation (NFC)
and Navashacti Picture Circuit of India signed here today a
40-million-Naira (about 470,000 U.S. Dollars) agreement on joint
production of film.
</P>
<P>
This is just part of NFC's efforts to break into the
international film market, said NFC Managing Director Brendan
Shehu, adding that each party would hold 50 percent equity in the
joint project.
</P>
<P>
The English-language feature film, "The Sacred stone", is
scheduled to start shooting in July and is expected to be out for
public view in December.
</P>
<P>
According to the News Agency of Nigeria, the film will be shot
in Nigeria and both local and foreign actors and actresses will
be employed. 
</P>
