<HEADLINE> Sudanese President Calls for Solidarity of Arab, Islamic States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese President Omar al Bashir
has called on leaders of Arab and Islamic states to bypass their
differences and unify their ranks to serve the ultimate causes of
the Islamic and Arab nations.
</P>
<P>
President Bashir said the Arab and Islamic states should do so
particularly during this period when hostile forces are joining
hands against the well-being of the Islamic and Arab world.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with the Qatari daily "Al Raya"
published today, President Bashir also said that Sudan was
endeavoring to restore its relations with Kuwait and remove the
present estrangement in the Sudanese-Egyptian relations, now that
inter-Arab relations are experiencing a state of relaxation,
according to Sudan News Agency.
</P>
<P>
He added that Sudan was at the same time reinstating its
relations with the neighboring African countries, and enchancing
and promoting the bonds of cooperation with other African states.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that Sudan will endeavor to restore unity and
solidarity of Arab ranks, and to develop its distinguished
relations with Asian and other countries of the world. 
</P>
