Also killed on the car was Christopher Feward, head of a
British Non-Governmental Organization OXFAM.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place near the central city of Benguela when
the U.N.peace keeping force members returned from the
supervision of the Angolan government troops going back to their
barracks.
</P>
<P>
The deaths leads to 4 the total number of the soldiers in the UN
peace keeping force killed in Angola. 
