<HEADLINE> Greece Expects Good Relations with Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 3 (Xinhua) --Greek government expressed today the
relations between Athens and Ankara must be improved and urged
Turkey to act in this direction.
</P>
<P>
"The government believes that the climate of tension and
friction in relations between Greece and Turkey must change and be
replaced by one of calm and the strengthening of ties and
friendship and cooperation,"government spokesman Dimitris Reppas
said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman added however that this could not be achieved
through "phrasal compliments", particularly when the latter were
accompanied by actions to the contrary.
</P>
<P>
"Greece has shown in practice and it respects the rules which
must constitutes the basis for a normalization of relations
between the two countries and Turkey must do the same," he said.
</P>
<P>
Reppas called on Turkey to sign the European Union text
concerning progress in the implementation of the EU-Turkey Customs
Union and to contribute to efforts and initiatives which have or
are to be undertaken for a just and viable solution to the Cyprus
problem.
</P>
<P>
He also urged Turkey to retract its threat that the extension
by Greece of its territorial waters in the Aegean from six to
twelve miles would be a casus belli for Ankara as well as to cease
its "violations of Greek air space and infringements of the Athens
flight information region (FIR)".
</P>
<P>
Lastly, he called on Turkey to clearly state that it harboured
no territorial designs against Greece, "as evidenced by its stance
in the recent Imia crisis and statements by Turkish officials
concerning the Dodecaneses in the Aegean." 
</P>
</TEXT>
