<HEADLINE> EU Annual Inflation Down to 2.7 Percent in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The European Union(EU) annual
inflation fell to 2.7 percent in February from 2.8 percent in
January, the Statistical Office of the European Communities in
Luxembourg(EUROSTAT), reported today.
</P>
<P>
EUROSTAT figures showed that in February inflation was below
the EU average in 11 member states.
</P>
<P>
Finland remained enjoying the lowest rate of 0.5 percent,
followed by Luxembourg and Germany, respectively at 1.0 percent
and 1.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Highest rate was of Greece, at 8.5 percent, with Italy next at
4.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
EUROSTAT pointed out that 2.7 percent is the lowest rate since
January 1987 and the rate has fallen steadily for more than five
years from a peak of 6.4 percent in October 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
