<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Namibia Chairs U.N.Working Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 3 (Xinhua)-- Namibia has been appointed to
chair a United Nations working group on an agenda for peace, the
South African Press Association reported today.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued in Windhoek,the Namibian Foreign Affairs
Ministry said the working group has been set up to re-evaluate
the U.N.'s role in promoting world peace, particularly its
prominent position in the prevention, mediation and resolution of
conflicts.
</P>
<P>
The group is one of five established to debate reform in the
world body.
</P>
<P>
Namibia succeeded Egypt in the chair of the working group.
</P>
<P>
''This appointment underscores the prestige and standing
Namibia enjoys in the international community and particularly at
the U.N.,'' said the statement.
</P>
<P>
It furthermore placed Namibia in the league of countries which
were shaping the destiny of the global governance body, it said.
</P>
