<HEADLINE> Ambassador of UN Volunteers Organization to Visit Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The honorary ambassador of the
United Nations Volunteers Organization, Takihutu Nakata, is due to
arrive here Saturday for a five-day visit to Yemen.
</P>
<P>
He is scheduled to inspect the activities undertaken by the
U.N. volunteers who are engaged in various projects in Yemen's
capital city of Sanaa, economic and trade center Aden and other
regions.
</P>
<P>
The honorary ambassador, a Japanese origin, is expected to meet
during his stay with officials in charge of the development
departments in the Yemeni Ministries of Foreign Affairs and
Planning and the governor of Aden to exchange views on the role of
the U.N. volunteers.
</P>
<P>
There are already 20 experts working as U.N. volunteers in
Yemen. They are taking part in the economic and social development
projects in such fields as water, sanitary drainage, health,
social development, mother and child care, tourism, hotel
management training, as well as seismology, dams, enrironment and
agriculture. These projects are being implemented by the United
Nations in partnership with the Yemeni government.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Nakata will hold meetings with the representatives
of the U.N. specialized agencies for further coordination and
expansion of the role of .U.N volunteers in the joint development
efforts between the United Nations and the Republic of Yemen.
</P>
