<HEADLINE> Denmark, Netherlands Provide Donations To UNDP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Denmark and the Netherlands
have contributed 17 million dollars to the United Nations
Development Program's "poverty strategies initiative", a plan
drawn to help countires formulate strategies to eradicate
absolute poverty, a press release from the UNDP office here said
today.
</P>
<P>
The money will, among other things, finance national public
awareness and advocate campaigns to mobilize organizations of
civil society, the private sector and other groups to join the
government in the fight against the poverty, the release said.
</P>
<P>
It noted that 25 million people each year join the 1.3 billion
people who live in absolute poverty in the countries of the
world.
</P>
<P>
The last United Nations general assembly has designated 1996
as the international year for the eradication of poverty, noting
the poverty eradication is fundamental to reinforcing peace and
achieving sustainable development. 
</P>
