<HEADLINE> UN Trade, Industry Agencies to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The UN Conference on Trade and
Development (UNCTAD) and the UN Industrial Development
Organization (UNIDO) announced here today an agreement to
strengthen their cooperative efforts to stimulate economic growth
in developing countries.
</P>
<P>
In a joint communique signed Wednesday by UNCTAD
Secretary-General Rubens Ricupero and UNIDO Director-General
Mauricio de Maria y Campos, the two organizations pledged to take
steps to strengthen complementarity between them.
</P>
<P>
By pooling their resources, the two organizations intend to
improve coordination for more effective technical assistance in
promoting industrial development and integrating developing
countries into the world trading system, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
The key areas envisaged for increased cooperation center on
science and technology, investment promotion and enterprise
development, especially small and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The communique also calls for an annual high-level meeting
between UNIDO and UNCTAD, chaired by their executive heads, for
regular consultations as well as for improving working
relationships between the two organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
