<HEADLINE> Water Supply Partially Resumed In Angolan Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Water supply was partially resumed
in the Angolan capital Luanda today after a two-week suspension.
</P>
<P>
Water supply in Luanda was suspended on March 18 after
succesive rains destroyed high-tension transmission lines in
the city.
</P>
<P>
To overcome difficulties caused by the water suspension, the
city government assembled a number of tank trucks to carry water
for the citizens. However, the water supplied was obtained from
rivers and it could not meet the demand of the citizens since it
was limited in quantity and inferior in quality.
</P>
<P>
As an emergency measure, the government installed diesel
generators in the city's running water plant to ensure
power supply. But the plant could not operate at its full
capacity, due to the shortage of power. enditem


