<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-03 17:07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier on SEZ's Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng urged special
economic zones to speed up their adjustment of product mix,
advancing new and hi-tech industries, and developing
higher-quality products to increase competitiveness both at home
and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came during Li's visit to Shenzhen, Zhuhai and
Zhongshan cities in south China's Guangdong Province, from March
30 to April 3.
</P>
<P>
Li was accompanied by Vice-Premier Li Lanqing and Xie Fei,
Guangdong Party Secretary and a member of the Political Bureau of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
The premier said that since the initiation of the opening up
and reform policy more than a decade ago, the economy in the
special economic zones and open coastal areas has been growing
rapidly and both the "hard" and "soft" environment for talents
and for investment has improved dramatically.
</P>
<P>
He noted that speeding up the pace of product mix adjustment
and improving products is imperative. Equally important is
encouraging ordinary processing industries to move to the central
and western parts of the country to develop new and hi-tech
industries, increasing development strength by using both domestic
and foreign funds, and applying advanced technology and management
expertise.
</P>
<P>
Li called on more prosperous areas to develop higher-quality
products and pillar industries, to set up a number of enterprise
groups to improve overall quality and efficiency, and make even
greater progress in developing an export-oriented economy.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that the coastal open areas should place cultural
and ideological progress in a more eminent position while
promoting material development.
</P>
<P>
Booming areas should still give free rein to the pioneering
spirit which was popular in the special economic zones at their
early stage, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Li went on to say that efforts should be made in enhancing
education to raise the quality of the whole people, improving all
facets of social security, and creating a better social
environment for investment, work, and living.
</P>
<P>
The premier pointed out that the special economic zones should
serve as examples in economic construction, opening-up, reforms,
and in cultural and ideological progress as well.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to the local customs, Li said it is necessary
to increase customs officials' competence and bring up to date the
equipment so as to beef up crackdown on smuggling activities with
coordinated efforts by relevant departments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
