<HEADLINE> URGENT: U.S. Commerce Secretary's Plane  Reportedly Missing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March (Xinhua)-- A plane carrying U.S. Commerce
Secretary Ron Brown crashed a few miles outside Dubrovnik,
Croatia, today, the Associated Press quoting diplomatic sources in
Europe reported.
</P>
<P>
The diplomatic source in Dubrovnik, Croatia said Brown's plane
went down in stormy weather near that city.
</P>
<P>
In Sarajevo, Capt. Jorst Fohmann, a spokesman for the NATO-led
forces in Bosnia, said that there had been a plane crash in a
mountainous area near Dubrovnik but was not able to confirm
whether that had been the plane carrying Brown from Tuzla, the
main base for U.S. troops in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
A Pentagon source said wreckage of a crashed plane had been
spotted in the area where Brown's plane was reported missing. But
this source, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the wreckage
had not been positively identified as the aircraft carrying Brown
and his entourage.
</P>
<P>
Because of the reported crash, U.S. President Clinton canceled
a noon appearance at the Justice Department where he was to
discuss anti-gang programs, Justice officials said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Commerce Secretary had planned to spend three days in
Bosnia and Croatia, meeting with American troops, government
figures and local business leaders. 
