<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-03 16:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Registers Candidacy for Russian Presidency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 3 (Xinhua) -- President Boris Yeltsin
officially registered himself as a candidate for the June
presidential polls at the Central Electoral Commission today.
</P>
<P>
The initiative group which nominated Yeltsin submitted the
registration documents and 1.37 million signatures in support of
his re-election bid, which was declared on February 15.
</P>
<P>
"Russia's fate depends on how people vote," Yeltsin told the
commission, "They can vote to keep the reins of power and they can
also vote to lose them."
</P>
<P>
Asked whether he was afraid of failure, Yeltsin told reporters,
"I am nervous because the fight will not be easy and rivals are
strong. But I am not scared and I will fight hard."
</P>
<P>
After registration, Yeltsin will have the right to formally
launch his re-election campaign. He is expected to declare his
election platform on April 6.
</P>
<P>
The only other candidate registered is Communist Party leader
Gennady Zyuganov, who is regarded as Yeltsin's strongest rival in
the presidential polls scheduled for June 16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
