<HEADLINE> Zambia Electricity Export Earnings Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Zambia's foreign exchange earnings
from export of electricity to its neighbors has been doubled in
the past four years, a Zambian minister revealed here today.
</P>
<P>
Energy and Water Development Minister Edith Nawakwi told
reporters here that the electricity export earnings have been
increased by 5.5 million US Dollars per year since 1991, bringing
the total annual amount to about 42 million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Nawakwi said before the present government came into power
more than four years ago, electricity exports stagnated at some
20 million Dollars per year.
</P>
<P>
This was a great improvement in power exports within the
period, she noted.
</P>
<P>
Nawakwi said the government intends to privatize state-owned
electricity companies in the long term, but the private sector is
now free to enter the power industry to generate electricity for
both home consumption and export.
</P>
<P>
She expressed hope that power exports would be boosted when
the private sector begins to participate in power generation.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Zambia exports electricity to Zimbabwe and
Tanzania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
