<HEADLINE> Indonesia's External Trade on Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's exports in January
rose to 3.58 billion US dollars while exports grew to 2.956
billion dollars, Information Minister Harmoko said today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total exports, oil commodities were valued at 933
million dollars and non-oil/gas-products were worth 2.647 billion
dollars, Harmoko told reporters after a cabinet meeting chaired by
President Soeharto.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country's imports rose to 2.956 billion dollars,
of which 2.765 billion dollars were from non-oil commodities.
</P>
<P>
During April 1995-January 1996, Indonesia enjoyed a trade
surplus of 4.177 billion US dollars, with the exports totalling
38.82 billion dollars and imports amounting to 34.646 billion
dollars.  
