President Boris Yeltsin, Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin,
Federation Council Speaker Yegor Stroyev and State Duma Speaker
Gennady Seleznev on bilateral relations and other issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
Russia is the second leg of Qiao's current tour, which will
also take him to Cuba and Canada. He earlier visited Kiev,
Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Qiao will meet with Yuri Klavtsov, chairman of the local
Legislative Council.
</P>
<P>
In St. Petersburg, the second largest city in Russia, Qiao will
also visit a number of historic sites, such as the Smolny Palace,
the Winter Palace and the Aurora Cruiser, which fired the first
shot during the October Revolution in 1917.
</P>
<P>
Qiao and his entourage leaves here for Athens, Greece, for a
stop-over before going on to Havana, Cuba.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
