<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host International Automotive Technology Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Encouraged by its success with two
previous auto shows, China has decided to hold a large-scale
international seminar and exhibition on automotive products,
development, and technology, between June 2 and 9 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Automotive Department of the Ministry of
Machine-building Industry said that China's auto industry entered
a new age with the promulgation of the "Automotive Industry
Policy" two years ago, and that China's plans to improve its auto
industry are greeted by much of the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
He said that the upcoming event will help domestic enterprises
keep abreast of trends in the international auto industry, and in
business opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The event has already attracted applications from the world's
top 20 auto manufacturers. Among them are the US's GM and Ford,
Japan's Toyota, Mitsubishi, and Isuzu, the Republic of Korea's
Daewoo and Hyundai, Italy's Fiat and Iveco, Germany's Volkswagen
and Audi, and Renault and Citroen of France.
</P>
<P>
Domestic auto groups will be showing their best products as
well. 
</P>
