<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Party Chief on Anti-Graft Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Party chief Wei Jianxing
said today that it is imperative that the supervisory mechanism of
the anti-graft campaign be improved.
</P>
<P>
Wei said at the Fourth Session of the 10th Beijing Municipal
People's Conference that former Party Secretary Chen Xitong's
problem and the case concerning former Vice-Mayor Wang Baosen
mirror the new issues arising in the Party and in political power
in the course of shifting from a planned economy to a
market-oriented one.
</P>
<P>
"We should increase democratic supervision, further improve the
supervisory mechanism, and gradually develop an effective system,
with laws and regulations on corruption to be enacted and improved
by learning from the past and gaining new experiences," he said.
</P>
<P>
The strengthening and reform on the supervisory mechanism must
be conducted on the basis of the Constitution and the Party
Constitution, meanwhile beefing up supervisory mechanism and
introducing and strengthening mechanism for inspiration and
encouragement, he said.
</P>
<P>
Although the emergence of the incident concerning Chen Xitong
and Wang Baosen is attributed to many factors, it involves the
question of supervision, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the leading cadres' political and ideological
building should be enhanced and importance attached to the
remoulding of their world outlook and outlook on life, and
democracy and legal development should be integrated, Wei said.
</P>
</TEXT>
