<HEADLINE> Chen Chalks up 3rd Gold, He Beaten at Champions' Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 3 (Xinhua/OANA) -- The 16-year-old Chen Yan
stole the limelight at the ongoing China's Champions' tourney as
she grabbed the third gold to her medal credit by winning the
women's 400 meters freestyle here Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Chen, a 1.78-meter triple-gold winner at last year's Urban
Games in Nanjing, clocked 4:11.33 to finish well ahead of second-
and third-placers Zhang Chanying and Wang Luna at 4:15.48 and
4:16.82 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Veteran Luo Ping, national 800m freestyle record holder and the
pre-competition favorite, had to settle for the fourth.
</P>
<P>
Chen, from Liaoning province in the northeastern China, swam
home the 400 meters individual medley gold on Monday and the 200m
freestyle on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The teenager has entered a total of five events at the Tianjin
tourney, with 200m individual medley and 800m freestyle, both
slated for Friday.
</P>
<P>
Another entry with the same pronunciation of Chen Yan, from
Jiangsu province in Southeastern China, also made a big splash in
the women's 100m backstroke, beating He Cihong to second.
</P>
<P>
He, world record holder of the event, finished atop after the
heats but struggled to the second place in the final at 1:02.98,
0.27 seconds behind Chen's 1:02.71
</P>
<P>
He was 2.82 seconds slower than her own world best of 1:00.16,
set at the World Championships in Rome two years ago.
</P>
<P>
However, she refused to comment on her performance.
</P>
<P>
"Obviously her time is slow," said Zhou Ming, vice head coach
of the Chinese team. "The result is disappointing for her."
</P>
<P>
Zhou also expressed concerns about the prospect of the Chinese
medley relay at the Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Lu Donghua shared the runner-up position with He by clocking
the same time.
</P>
<P>
The men's 100m freestyle title went to national 100m butterfly
record holder Jiang Chengji at 51.21 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Xie Xufeng, from Guangdong province, chalked up the men's 200m
butterfly crown with a modest time of 2:02.72.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, competitors will vie for the titles in the men's
400m freestyle, 100m backstroke, 4x100 freestyle relay and women's
200m breaststroke and 100m butterfly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
