<HEADLINE> Nepal Introduces Forest Management Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Nepal has introduced a forest
management plan in the southern Terai plain region with the aim
of achieving sustainable development of the country's abundant
forest resources.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement of the Ministry of Forest and Soil
Conservation today, the forest management plan prepared for six
districts of the Terai region would improve the ecological status
of forests there and help maintain a healthy environment in the
country.
</P>
<P>
It would push the country forward along the path of sustainable
economic development, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Under the new plan, scientific management measures would be
introduced in order to reap maximum economic returns.
</P>
<P>
A forest resources development committee has already been set
up under the Forest Ministry and it has implemented scientific
management to some 7,500 hectares of forest in the region, added
the statement.
</P>
<P>
The government would adopt similar management for a total of
4,255 hectares of deteriorating forest in southern Nepal in the
near future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
