<HEADLINE> Qiao: China Values Ties With Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ST. PETERSBURG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislator Qiao
Shi said here today that China values friendly and mutually
beneficial relations with its great neighbor, Russia.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, Chairman of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee was holding talks with Yuri Klavtsov, chairman
of the local Legislative Council.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said the frequent exchange of visits by leaders of both
countries has added new momentum to the development of a
constructive partnership between China and Russia oriented toward
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Qiao flew in earlier today from Moscow, where he had talks with
President Boris Yeltsin and Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin on
bilateral relations and other issues of common concern. He also
met Federation Council Speaker Yegor Stroyev and State Duma
Speaker Gennady Seleznev.
</P>
<P>
"Inter-parliamentary contacts, as a major part of
state-to-state relations, have contributed to the healthy and
smooth development of Sino-Russian ties," Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the courage and endurance of the people of
St. Petersburg during the Second World War were known to all in
China. St. Petersburg withstood a 900-day siege by Nazi troops
during the war.
</P>
<P>
Russia is the second leg of Qiao's tour, which has taken him to
Ukraine and will also take him to Cuba and Canada.
</P>
<P>
Qiao will meet with St. Petersburg Mayor Anatoly Sobchak
Thursday and leave here Friday for Athens for a stop-over. 
</P>
</TEXT>
