<HEADLINE> International Symposium on Education Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- An international symposium on
education was held here today to mark the tenth anniversary of the
State Education Development Center.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 scholars and educators from the United States,
the Republic of Korea, and the Chinese mainland and Hong Kong
delivered reports on education development in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Agreement was reached on the necessity and benefit of China's
cooperating with other countries on educational development and
reforms.
</P>
<P>
Since 1986, when it was set up, the center has been responsible
for research on key State education policies, and did a series of
surveys on education development targets for the 1990s and the
next century. A number of the research results have been used for
policy making.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng and other high-ranking officials, wrote
inscriptions for the center.
</P>
