<HEADLINE> Romania Supports China's Stance on Taiwan Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Romania regards Taiwan as part
of China and has always supported China's stance on the issue of
Taiwan, President Ion Iliescu said here today.
</P>
<P>
Iliescu told reporters that he appreciated the policies of
"peaceful reunification and one China, two systems" pursued by the
Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
He said the policies have proven effective in Hong Kong, a
British colony due to revert to Chinese sovereignty in 1997, and
could be applied to the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Further strengthening ties across the Taiwan Straits will be
helpful to both sides, he added.
</P>
<P>
The president said Romania and China have good relations and
share common views on all issues. 
</P>
