<HEADLINE> New Committee for Improving Mineral Resources Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua
announced at a national meeting here today that the State Council
has decided to set up a National Committee on Mineral Resources as
a means of improving the sector.
</P>
<P>
The new committee will replace the existing National Committee
on Mineral Reserves, and will mainly be involved in research on
mineral resource policies, and protection and development of
resources for a certain period of time. It will also coordinate
efforts in this sector between different departments and regions.
</P>
<P>
Zou urged members of the new committee to come up with more
useful policies, systems, and strategies for the industry to raise
it to a higher level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
