<DOCNO> XIE19960403.0083 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-03 14:45 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Training Sessions for Seven Hundred Mayors in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Over the past five years, a total
of 700 mayors and vice-mayors in China got advanced training in
urban planning and city management.
</P>
<P>
Another 800 will receive training over the next five years,
according to the country's plans.
</P>
<P>
The program was sponsored by the Organization Department of the
Communist Party of China Central Committee, the Ministry of
Construction, and the China Association for Science and
Technology, as a means of improving the overall level of city
management in the country.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China now has 640 cities, nearly 200 more
than it had in 1990, and although 80 percent of the mayors and
vice-mayors of these cities graduated from universities or
colleges, few of them majored in city management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
