<DOCNO> XIE19960403.0084 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-03 14:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fewer Crimes in Kazakhstan in 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of criminal cases in
Kazakhstan fell to 183,000 in 1995, a decrease of 8.9 percent from
the previous year, the Ministry of Internal Affairs said.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics recently released by the ministry,
cases of murder and attempted murder dropped 4 percent. Cases of
rape and theft fell 7.3 and 18.2 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The ministry attributed this to the government's intensified
anti-crime efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Caravan Express newspaper said that 41,000 people were
sentenced to prison terms, 18,000 sent to reform-through-labor
camps and 9,000 were fined. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
