<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stamps Show to Mark anniversary of HK China Philatelic Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A large stamp show opened here
today to mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the Hong
Kong-based China Philatelic Association.
</P>
<P>
Jointly organized by the association and the Commercial Press
Hong Kong Ltd., the 10-day show presents various types of
commemorative stamps with a focus on saving dolphin and whales in
the ocean.
</P>
<P>
It presents various stamps about dolphin and whales published
by all countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
The show also highlights stamps about "Scenery in Hong Kong",
as well as some rare sets of stamps published by China's Qing
Dynasty in 1878, a set of British Queen's Portrait published in
Hong Kong in 1891, and commemorative stamps published in China's
Liberated Areas in 1938.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five decades, the China Philatelic Association
has played an active role in organizing activities among the stamp
 funs through stamp-exchange gatherings, philatelic symposiums and
 stamps shows. It also publishes philatelic periodicals in Chinese
 in Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
