<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Death Toll in South Korean Bus Accident Reaches 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 3 (Xinhua) -- At least 13 people have been
confirmed dead and 45 others injured when a South Korean
inter-city bus plunged into the Namhan River near Yangpyong city
about 40 kilometers west of Seoul.
</P>
<P>
The bus, carrying some 60 people, including students and
shoppers returning from the market, fell into the icy river around
5:30 p.m. local time, a police spokesman was quoted as saying by
reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said he feared the death toll may rise as some
passengers may have fallen out of the bus into the river as the
vehicle rolled down the embankment.
</P>
<P>
Local policemen and soldiers and an army helicopter were
engaged in the rescue operation.
</P>
<P>
Some reports said that the accident might have been caused by
speeding, but the exact cause is still under investigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
