<DOCNO> XIE19960403.0090 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-03 14:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> GCC Takes Precaution against Mad Cow Disease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Livestock Committee of the
Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) started a meeting today in Riyadh
to take joint precautions against the Mad Cow disease.
</P>
<P>
According to Kuwait News Agency, the GCC General Secretariat
proposed the urgent meeting after receiving requests in this
regard from Bahrain and Oman.
</P>
<P>
The one-day meeting will discuss the consequences of the
disease in the Gulf region and adopt a common position in this
regard.
</P>
<P>
GCC states have declared a ban on imports of British Beef, in
which scientists have declared that they found a link between the Mad
Cow disease with the Creutzfeld-Jakob Disease (CJD), which can
cause brain damage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
