<HEADLINE> Li Sets Goals for Shanghai Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference urged Shanghai to contribute more to national economic
development by the turn of the century today, during a visit to
the country's largest metropolitan area and business center.
</P>
<P>
Li, also member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, said
great efforts made by the people of Shanghai have helped to meet
Deng Xiaoping's call for Shanghai to have "a change in one year,
and a major change in three years" during the Eighth Five-Year
Plan (1991-1995).
</P>
<P>
Li also pointed out that Shanghai is bound to become an
international economic, financial, and trade center in the near
future, as long as it complies with Deng's theory and instructions.
</P>
<P>
He noted that there are both advantages and disadvantages for
the metropolis in carrying out the Ninth Five-Year Plan
(1996-2000) and the Long-Term Goals to the Year 2010.
</P>
<P>
As an economic giant, Shanghai should be bold enough to have
more experience to serve the national development, and should play
a more significant role, Li said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
