<HEADLINE> HK Link with Shanghai ATM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Visitors from Hong Kong with
Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corp. credit cards can now get cash
from Industrial and Commercial Bank of China's ATMs in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The link-up was made today and is the first time for a Shanghai
bank to be connected with banks outside the Chinese mainland via
the ATM network.
</P>
<P>
Withdrawals from the machines are limited to 3,000 yuan each
time and 10,000 Hongkong dollars' worth of yuan per day.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the link will not only be more
convenient for customers, but will promote financial cooperation
between the two cities.
</P>
<P>
The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation Ltd. has 600
representative offices in 19 countries in Asia, and is the largest
bank in Hong Kong. It also has a branch in Shanghai. It issues 13
different kinds of cards in Hong Kong and has more than three
million card holders.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, some 200,000 people from Hong Kong
visit Shanghai every year. The official predicts that further
economic cooperation will bring even more people from Hong Kong in
the next few years.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai branch of the Industrial and Commercial Bank of
China has opened some 600 offices and installed 320 ATMs in the
city. Last year, it was linked up with other large banks in the
city via the ATM network.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
