<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Cathay Pacific Airways, the flag
carrier of Hong Kong, has ordered a multi-million dollar flight
simulator for its new pilot training center from CAE Electronics
of Canada.
</P>
<P>
Today's South China Morning Post reported that the full flight
simulator, for Airbus A330 aircraft, will be delivered this summer
and will initially be installed at Cathay's pilot training center
at Kai Tak airport before being moved once the new airport at Chek
Lap Kok opens in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The airline short-listed two sites in Hong Kong for its one
billion HK dollars pilot training center, but has not made a final
decision.
</P>
<P>
The new center will contain about 14 flight simulators
representing the airline's fleet of Boeing and Airbus jet-liners.
