<HEADLINE> South Korea Receives More Construction Orders From Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 3 (Xinhua) -- South Korea has received 32 overseas
construction contracts worth 2.94 billion U.S. dollars in the
first quarter of this year, an increase of more than 300 percent
in value from the same period last year, the Ministry of
Construction and Transportation said today.
</P>
<P>
Asia is the largest market for South Korean builders,
accounting for 2.49 billion dollars or 85 percent of the total for
the three-month period, according to the ministry.
</P>
<P>
South Korea's Daewoo Construction Company took the top spot
with 1.63 billion dollars or 55 percent of the January-March
total, followed by Dong Ah with 513 million dollars, Hyundai with
429 million and Sangyong with 126 million.
</P>
<P>
The country is expected to receive a total of 10.8 billion
dollars worth of overseas construction orders this year, up 26.9
percent from last year.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, construction firms received overseas orders worth 8.51
billion dollars, 13.9 percent more than the previous year's 7.47
billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
