<HEADLINE> Pakistan Power Supplier Privatization by December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 3 (Xinhua) - The process of privatization of
Karachi Electric Supply Corporation (KESC) is expected to be
completed by the end of 1996, said Federal Secretary of the
Pakistani Ministry of Water and Power Ashfaq Mehmood today.
</P>
<P>
Briefing the Sindh provincial senate in the southern port city
of Karachi, Ashfaq said that the government has appointed a
financial advisory committee which will prepare a report on the
liabilities and assets of KESC within three months.
</P>
<P>
The Associated Press of Pakistan quoted him as saying the
government has not decided yet if KESC should be privatized as it
is or to privatize its generation and distribution systems
separately.
</P>
<P>
KESC is one of the major organizations in the country involved
in generation, transmission and distribution of electric energy.
</P>
<P>
Its total assets is 946 million US dollars with a total
generation capacity of 1,736 Megawatts and 1.2 million customers.
 
</P>
