<HEADLINE> China to Conduct Survey of Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China will launch its first ever
national survey of agriculture next January, in order to provide
objective data for government policy making.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Vice-premier Jiang Chunyun in a national
telephone meeting today. He said that great changes have taken
place in China's agriculture, and that the data the government now
holds may not be as trustworthy as necessary.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he doubts the credibility of the official figure for
China's farmland area, which is put at 928.67 million hectares.
"People from all social sectors deem the figure as relatively
lower than the actual one," he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged all local governments to provide adequate funding for
the massive statistical operation, and called on them to take
effective measures to spread the knowledge about what an
agricultural survey is about.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the survey will cover more than 200 million
rural households, and over 20 million village and township-level
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The total population to be targeted is some 900 million, and
more than six million statistics workers will be involved in the
survey, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
