<HEADLINE> EU Won't Lift Ban on British Beef Soon: French Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will not
lift its ban on British beef exports within the next six weeks,
French Agriculture Minister Philippe Vasseur said today.
</P>
<P>
Vasseur was speaking to reporters in Luxembourg, where EU farm
ministers are holding discussions to resolve the crisis over mad
cow disease.
</P>
<P>
The ministers thrashed out a package of measures today to put
beef back on European tables. They demanded that Britain kill all
cattle more than three months old and submit to the EU a detailed
plan for the mass slaughter no later than April 30.
</P>
<P>
The ministers also decided that a special committee under the
European Commission will consider extension of the ban when it is
due.
</P>
<P>
These measures indicated that all EU countries had given top
priority to public health and consumers' interests, Vasseur said.
</P>
</TEXT>
