<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Office of the Philippine
Ombudsman will start a preliminary investigation into the
involvement of seven health officials, including former Health
Secretary Hilarion Ramiro, in the alleged irregular procurement of
"medikits" in November 1995.
</P>
<P>
A three-man panel, headed by Director of the Evaluation and
Preliminary Investigation Bureau Angel Mayoralgo, has been set up
and will start a formal probe into the issue within 60 days.
</P>
<P>
The seven officials of the Health Department are implicated in
the purchase of some 4,500 medical kits worth 11.8 million pesos
(472,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Ombudsman will also determine whether or not Alicia
Cabahug, owner of the trading company that retailed the medikits,
should be charged with bribing the health officials.  
