<HEADLINE> Gazzetta dello Sport Marks 100th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Gazzetta dello Sport, the oldest
sports daily in the world, marked its 100th birthday on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Italian paper, which is known as "La Rosea" for its pink
pages, published an 124-page celebratory edition headlined
"Gazzettissima 100".
</P>
<P>
"The Gazzetta of our grandfathers and fathers has become not
only part of Italy's heritage but also that of the world," said
editor Candido Cannavo on the front page.
</P>
<P>
The paper was founded just three days before the first modern
Olympic Games in Athens in 1896 after merging two smaller
newspapers.
</P>
<P>
The paper, whose page color turned pink in 1900, also initiated
the famous "Giro d'Italia" (Tour of Italy) cycling race in 1909.
</P>
<P>
The paper sold the most copies, 1,486,110 to be exact, in 1989
when AC Milan soccer club won the European Cup.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's special edition was still priced at 1,400 lire and
a commemorative Italian postage stamp was also issued. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
