<DOCNO> XIE19960403.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-03 12:02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Compiles First Records of Lakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The first national record of
China's 2,800 lakes, after the founding of the People's Republic
of China in 1949, has been published in Nanjing, capital city of
east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The book was jointly compiled by the Nanjing Institute of
Geography and Lakes, Institute of Surveying and Geology and
Institute of Saline Lakes under the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
There are over 2,800 lakes each with an area of more than one
square kilometer in China, totalling 82,000 sq km in area.
</P>
<P>
More than 700 of them have an area of more than ten sq km each,
totalling 76,000 sq km in area.
</P>
<P>
So far, China's research of lakes has concentrated on more than
50 in economically developed east China. The book is expected to
promote China's research in the field, as well as into
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The book consists of two parts and contains 350 illustrations
and pictures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
