<HEADLINE> Manila to Grant Two-Year Visas to Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government will
grant two-year visas with multiple entry privileges to foreign
investors to press its drive to attract more foreign investment,
official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The privileges will also be extended to aliens working for
foreign companies in the Philippines as part of the incentives for
foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
According to Mel Rima, spokesman of the Immigration Bureau, one
of the primary complaints of the foreign investors here is the
bureaucratic red tape, especially on visas and other entry
procedures.
</P>
<P>
To set up the mechanics and procedure for the new system, the
Philippine Board of Investments, Department of Labor and
Employment and the Bureau of Immigration will sign an agreement
defining their respective functions and responsibilities, said the
sources.  
