<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-03 11:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Total Moon Eclipse in Hong Kong on Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A total lunar eclipse will occur
in Hong Kong Thursday morning, according to the Hong Kong
Observatory.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the observatory said that at 6:21 a.m. Thursday,
the moon enters umbra and at 7:27 a.m., total eclipse begins.
Total eclipse ends at 8:53 a.m. and the moon leaves umbra at 9:59
a.m.
</P>
<P>
He said that as the time of occurrence will be from 7:27 a.m.
to 8:53 a.m. Thursday, one hour after local moon sets, the total
eclipse will not be visible in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The next lunar eclipse visible in Hong Kong will be on
September 17, 1997, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
