<HEADLINE> Investments in Philippine Economic Zones Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Investments in the Philippine
economic zones stood at 7.789 billion pesos (311.56 million US
dollars) in the first three months of 1996, 16.6 percent up from
the 6.681 billion pesos (267.24 million dollars) posted a year
ago.
</P>
<P>
According to the Philippine Economic Zone Authority, some 44
new enterprises set up shops in the government-run zones and
private-owned industrial estates during the period, most of which
were registered as export-oriented firms.
</P>
<P>
During the same period in 1995, only 35 new firms made their
entry into the economic zones.
</P>
<P>
Government officials noted that there is growing interest in
establishing economic zone support projects for the needs of the
locators.
</P>
<P>
These economic zone enterprises include facilities for lease,
developers and operators and service companies.  
