<HEADLINE> Malaysia Can Become Capital Market Center: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia today said it can
become a well developed capital market center like Singapore and
Hong Kong based on its advantages.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's Finance Ministry Parliament Secretary Shafie Mohd
Salleh told the parliament during question time here that the
advantages included political and economic stability and the eight
percent annual economic growth rate for the past eight consecutive
years.
</P>
<P>
He also said the Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange also recorded
encouraging capital market turnover of 213 billion US dollars last
year, becoming the fourth biggest stock market in the Asia-Pacific
region and the 16th biggest in the world.
</P>
<P>
He also told the parliament that the government has taken
various programs and measures to ensure that Malaysia becomes an
ideal capital market with credibility, efficiency, stability and
responsibility.
</P>
<P>
The programs included the development of a fund management
industry and a competitive and dynamic derivative financial
market, and the development of a capital market based on the
Islamic principles, he added. 
