<HEADLINE> hke040338 --Sri Lanka, Switzerland Renew Repatriation Arrangement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka and Switzerland have
agreed to renew the bilateral arrangement for the repatriation of
rejected asylum seekers to Sri Lanka, a news release said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The release said that the Sri Lankan Foreign Ministry
communicated to the Swiss embassy in Colombo the government's
agreement to extend the bilateral arrangement for a further period
of two years.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken following an official communication sent
by the director of Switzerland's Federal Office for Refugees to
the Sri Lanka Consulate in Geneva in consideration of the present
situation in Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Following the decision taken last month by the Swiss Federal
Office for Refugees to recommence repatriation, the bilateral
arrangement has been renewed for another two years effective April
2 this year, said the release adding that the number of persons to
be repatriated under the new arrangement will be determined
following bilateral consultations.  
</P>
