<HEADLINE> Road Order Improving in Liaoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Drivers will no longer suffer
from being randomly fined on roads in northeast China's Liaoning
Province, as a drive to promote traffic order has taken effect.
</P>
<P>
Like busy roads in other parts of China, roads here were once
filled with unauthorized checkpoints.
</P>
<P>
In a drive to protect the interests of drivers, the provincial
traffic authorities removed 403 unlawful checkpoints.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
