<HEADLINE> Mubarak Meets with Tunisian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak met
here this morning with visiting Tunisian Prime Minister Hamed
Karoui for talks on bilateral relations as well as regional and
international issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Karoui said following the meeting that Tunisia and Egypt will
sign a number of cooperation agreements in trade, finance and
tourism.
</P>
<P>
Karoui, who arrived in Cairo Tuesday on a two-day visit to
Egypt, is to co-chair meetings of the Higher Egyptian-Tunisian
Committee with his Egyptian counterpart Kamal el-Ganzouri. 
</P>
