<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greening Program Makes Progress In Maldives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 3 (Xinhua)-- More than 97,000 trees of different
species have been planted in the Maldives so far under the
"million tree greening program", according to a news release
reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The release said these trees include 4,423 palm trees, 8,400
fruit trees and more than 83,900 timber saplings.
</P>
<P>
The million tree program is to be carried out with special
efforts in the nine selected atolls and in Kaashidhoo island where
land is available, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The program, to be carried out within the next three years, was
 inaugurated by President M.A.Gayoom on January 15 of this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
