<HEADLINE> More Qualified Teachers in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is scoring high marks for
improving the quality of local teachers in schools across the city.
</P>
<P>
It follows an initiative by the local municipal government to
improve learning at schools of different levels of learning.
</P>
<P>
Local government's departments said the number of university
and college qualified teachers in senior middle schools improved
from 43 percent in 1980 to 74 percent in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The rate in junior middle schools went up from 31 percent to 82
percent, while in primary schools, the rate rose from 66 percent
to 93 percent.
</P>
<P>
Marked increases have been recorded in the number of teachers
with senior professional titles in universities and colleges,
under direct administration of local municipal government.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the proportion of professors to the total
number of teachers increased from 1.4 percent to 6.4 percent
during the 1986-1994 period; the ratio of associate professors
went up from 12.2 percent to 30.6 percent. The number of teachers
with middle-ranking and senior professional titles amounted to 67
percent of total number of teacher in schools for adults.
</P>
<P>
To strengthen building of teaching groups, the municipal
government has established systems to recognize the qualifications
of teachers, and the ranking of their duties. More measures have
also been taken to award teachers who have made remarkable
academic progress and achievements.  
</P>
</TEXT>
