<HEADLINE> Worker Collects 5,000 Ancient Coins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Factory worker Qi Weizhi is in
the money, after amassing a collection of more than 5,000 ancient
coins.
</P>
<P>
The 56-year-old worker at an iron and steel plant in northeast
China's Liaoning Province started his coin collection over 40
years ago.
</P>
<P>
Experts said it is very rare for an individual, a worker in
particular, to collect so many ancient coins by himself.
</P>
<P>
It all started for Qi Weizhi when he was kicking a shuttlecock
which was made of a chain of coins.
</P>
<P>
Since then, he has gone all out to maintain his hobby, and all
his savings have been used in coin collecting. He has been
described as a super-fan of coin collecting.
</P>
<P>
To understand every word on the coins, he has read his
dictionary so much that it has virtually fallen to pieces. So far,
he has kept coins of nearly all the dynasties in Chinese history.
</P>
<P>
Recently, Qi was honored as the "Worker Collector" for his
knowledge on ancient coins, and rich coin collection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
