<HEADLINE> Secret Group Threatens Zambian Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A secret group in Zambia, called
"black mamba" (poisonous snake), has threatened to eliminate
ministers and the speaker of the National Assembly if they
insisted on adopting the draft constitution through Parliament,
the "Zambia Daily Mail" reported today.
</P>
<P>
So far, 10 ministers or deputy ministers and Speaker of the
National Assembly Robinson Nubulyato are among those who have
received the death threats through anonymous letters, according
to the daily.
