<HEADLINE> Inter-Bank Money Market Active in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Total trading on China's national
inter-bank money market reached 38.437 billion yuan (about 4.6
billion US dollars) in March, said an official source here.
</P>
<P>
He said capital trading on the market, which was electronically
hooked up to 19 banks and 35 regional money centers on March 1,
was "active" and daily transactions kept growing throughout the 21
trading days.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that the role of the money centers was reinforced
last month. Their borrowing and lending accounted for 92.78
percent and 79.28 percent of the total, respectively.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, trading in money in terms longer than one
month was 71.53 percent of the monthly trading volume.
</P>
<P>
The inter-bank money market has been in trial operation for
three months.  
</P>
