<HEADLINE> India's Exports of Livestock, Meats to Cross 144.9  Million Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- India's exports of livestock and
meats are likely to exceed 5,000 million rupees (144.9 million US
dollars) during the current financial year compared with 4,480
million rupees (129.9 million dollars) recorded during the
financial year 1994-95, according to a press release by meat
exporters here today.
</P>
<P>
The major increase in livestock product exports is expected to
be in buffalo meat, followed by sheep and goat meat.
</P>
<P>
India has the livestock population of 430 million, the second
largest in the world, but its export share in the world market is
very small due to poor livestock management and lack of mechanized
and automated abattoir facilities, the release said.
</P>
<P>
India exports livestock products mainly to Malaysia, UAE, the
Philippines, Oman, Saudi Arabia, Mauritius and Kuwait.  
</P>
