<HEADLINE> Philadelphia's Stackhouse Named Rookie of the Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Jerry Stackhouse of the
Philadelphia 76er on Tuesday was named the Rookie of the Month for
March.
</P>
<P>
Stackhouse, the third selection in the 1995 NBA Draft, averaged
22.3 points, 4.5 assists, 4.1 rebounds, 1.3 blocked shots and 1.2
steals per game in 15 games of the month.
</P>
<P>
He ranked first in scoring and third in assists among rookie
league-leaders during March.
</P>
<P>
"He has many of the moves that rookies don't get for several
years and he'll be an outstanding player when he continues to
mature," said Philadelphia Head Coach John Lucas of Stackhouse.
</P>
<P>
During the month, Stackhouse had 30 or more points three times
and 20 or more points 11 times. He led Philadelphia in scoring
eight times, in rebounding six times and in assists two times.
</P>
<P>
Among other Candidates for Rookie of the Month were Boston's
Eric Williams, Clevland's Bob Sura, Denver's Antonio McDyess and
Golden State's Joe Smith. 
</P>
