construction of Large industrial projects in the island province
of Hainan at the southernmost tip of China.
</P>
<P>
The province has set the goal of making this, China's biggest
special economic zone an emerging industrial power in the next
five years.
</P>
<P>
Construction of large industrial projects is the first step
toward the goal and such projects will not only propel faster
economic expansion, but lay the foundation for Hainan's industry.
</P>
<P>
Hainan is to build 30 major construction projects costing some
five billion yuan this year, among which 13 will be large
industrial ones.
</P>
<P>
Eight of the 13 will have their construction continued this
year, and most of them will be put into operation next year. Some
leading projects include a refinery with a total investment of
12.8 billion yuan and a chemical fertilizer plant costing 1.7
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Five new projects will be started within this year with each
involving an investment of at least one billion yuan.  
