<HEADLINE> Book on Late Marshal Chen Yi Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A book titled "Chronicle of Chen
Yi" appeared Tuesday to commemorate the 95th anniversary of the
birthday of the late marshal (1901-1972).
</P>
<P>
The book, compiled by Liu Shufa, a research fellow at the
Social Sciences Academy of China, and published by the People's
Publishing House, is the first detailed account of the life and
career of Chen, one of the ten marshals of the People's Republic
of China.
</P>
<P>
The chronicle, based upon reliable historical documents and
files, presents an authentic record of the late marshal's
revolutionary life and sings the praises of his lofty spirit. At
the same time it illustrates one aspect of the arduous Chinese
revolutionary course in the earlier part of this century.
</P>
<P>
The book took Liu and his colleagues six years to complete.
</P>
<P>
Some veteran leaders, most of whom were friends and
subordinates of the late marshal, attended yesterday's public
ceremony for the launch of the book. 
</P>
