<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China has become the world's
largest producer of edible fungus, knocking Japan off the top spot.
</P>
<P>
Edible fungus has become one of the three most profitable farm
produces in China, with yearly output topping three million tons.
</P>
<P>
China exports 250,000 tons of mushrooms valued at 400 million
US dollars a year, a report in "Market Daily" revealed.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Japan has averaged 8,000 tons in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Panyu and Huidong cities in south China's Guangdong Province
have built a number of gardens, catering for the production of
Golden Needle mushrooms which sell well in Hong Kong.  
