<HEADLINE> India's Industrial Output Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- India's industrial production
registered a growth rate of 11.7 percent from April to November
last year, up from 9.5 percent in the corresponding period of the
previous year, sources from the Indian Central Statistical
Organization said today.
</P>
<P>
The country's average industrial index from April to November,
1995, stood at 267.3, compared with 239.4 for the corresponding
period of the previous year, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
In the same period, industrial production in the manufacturing
sector registered a growth rate of 12.5 percent, up from 10.1
percent in the corresponding period in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The production of consumer durables registered an impressive
growth rate of 31 percent, compared with 12 percent previously.
