<P>
In their presentations to the government, the foreign bankers
made out a strong case for setting right the lopsided nature of
tariff that makes the charges for local calls disproportionately
higher but keeps the long-distance charges lower.
</P>
<P>
The foreign bankers, who may have to provide 80 percent of the
funding of 15 billion US dollars necessary in the first five
years, have expressed their inability to tie up the funds without
removal of the skew in the tariff structure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
