<HEADLINE> Thai Finance Ministry to Issue Independent Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Thai Finance Minister Surakiart
Sathirathai has said that his ministry will publish its own
economic reports every quarter beginning this year.
</P>
<P>
The finance minister made this announcement according to an
agreement reached among Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation finance
ministers recently in Japan.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Ministry will start to inform the public of raw
economic figures, including debts and revenues, on July 20,
without any prior analysis, he said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The figures from the Finance Ministry will be different from
those from the Central Bank and the Commerce Ministry, the two
major government agencies currently reporting economic figures to
the public, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Central bank mainly reveals financial figures for the
country and the Commerce Ministry reports figures like consumer
price index (CPI) and gross domestic product (GDP). 
