<HEADLINE> First Sino-Foreign Research Institute Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The first Sino-foreign research
institute, the Joint Telecommunications Technology Laboratory, has
been set up here, according to the overseas edition of today's
"People's Daily".
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the laboratory was launched jointly by the
State Intelligence Computer Research and Development Center and
the Motorola Company of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Initially, the center will concentrate on developing
high-performance telecommunications products for both domestic and
international markets.
</P>
<P>
The two partners each will have 50 percent of the intellectual
property rights to be created by the center.
</P>
<P>
Motorola has decided to install its most sophisticated know-how
in the laboratory and send 10 engineers to work together with
their 10 Chinese colleagues in the laboratory. 
</P>
