Thousands of Northeastern farmers, slum-dwellers, dam-affected
villagers and laid-off workers have joined forces in the protest.
</P>
<P>
As the protest continues, Metropolitan Police Bureau officers
said the demonstrators were unlikely to go home soon because their
demands could not be tackled in a short time.
</P>
<P>
Responding to the protesters' threat to break into Government
House, Metropolitan police sources said that police are prepared
to cope with possible unrest.  
