<HEADLINE> Portland's Sabonis Named NBA Player of the Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Portland's Arvydas Sabonis edged
out Miami's Alonzo Mourning for NBA Player of the Week honors for
the week ending on Sunday, March 31.
</P>
<P>
Sabonis, who helped lead Portland to a 4-0 record for the week,
averaged 20.3 points, 9.5 rebounds, 2.3 blocked shots and 2.0
assists in 27.8 minutes per game. The 7-3 center shot 0.648 from
the field and 0.429 from three-point range.
</P>
<P>
Portland, winners of four consecutive games, has won nine of
its last ten games since the rookie from Lithuania was inserted
into the starting lineup on March 8.
</P>
<P>
Mourning averaged 31.7 points, 12.7 rebounds and 2.3 blocked
shots in leading Miami to a 2-1 record last week. He scored a
career-high 50 points in Miami's 112-93 defeat of Washington on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Among other candidates for NBA Player of the Week were Boston's
David Wesley and the Los Angeles Laker's Earvin Johnson. 
</P>
