<HEADLINE> Nepali Government to Finance Rural Development  Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Nepali government has
allocated the budget for a nationwide rural development program
aimed at giving more autonomy to the country's nearly 4,000
villages, according to the Local Development Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The rural self reliance program, introduced in the government's
budget report for the 1995-96 fiscal year ending in coming July,
provided the estabishing of a village development fund for each
village in the country with government assistance of at least
500,000 rupees (10,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Under the program, villages would invest development projects
under their own initiatives.
</P>
<P>
The government had earmarked 2,014 million rupees (40 million
dollars) for the program, a spokesman of the Local Development
Ministry said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The main objective of the rural self reliance program is to
prioritize the role of village administrations in the development
work and assist them to formulate specific development projects,
according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He said the ministry had requested all villages to submit their
detailed reports on development to receive the allocated budget.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
