<HEADLINE> Slovakia Bans Beef Imports in Mad Cow Scare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia today announced an
immediate ban on the imports of cattle and beef products from
Britain or other countries where the mad cow disease has been
discovered.
</P>
<P>
The Slovak government said that the ban is aimed to protect its
citizens from the attacks of the mad cow disease which is causing
a worldwide panic.
</P>
<P>
The government ordered the Ministry of Agriculture to take
measures to identify the countries affected by the ban.
</P>
<P>
Ever before the announcement of the ban, the beef sales in
Slovakia had already shrunk dramatically. 
