<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-03 03:07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Industrial Exports Up in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports reached 239.5
billion baht (9.58 billion U.S. dollars) in value in the first two
months this year, up 19.9 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Commerce Ministry, exports of industrial
products reached 148.69 billion baht (5.95 billion dollars) in
value, up 27.9 percent during the period compared with the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The fast-growing exports were computers and parts, integrated
circuits, plastics, gems and jewelry, frozen shrimps, canned food,
video and stereo equipment, textiles and air-conditioner units.
</P>
<P>
Yet, agricultural exports declined 7.1 percent to 35.75 billion
baht (1.43 billion dollars) in value during the first two months
this year, mainly due to drops in rice and rubber exports.
</P>
<P>
Rubber exports decreased by 12.5 percent in volume and 17.3
percent in value during the period, while rice exports fell 29.3
percent in volume and 5 percent in value.
</P>
<P>
Exports of agro-industrial products rose 11.7 percent to 19.48
billion baht (779.2 million dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
