<HEADLINE> Becker Back to Germany for Medical Examination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Boris Becker might miss Germany's
Davis Cup Quarter-final against France after he returned to Munich
for a medical examination on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Germany and France are scheduled to play on an indoor clay
court starting Friday. The draw is set for Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Becker was forced to withdraw from two tournaments in the
United States due to bronchitis after winning the Australian Open
last January.
</P>
<P>
Becker, a three-time Wimbledon winner, arrived in Limoges,
France, Sunday night and had a light workout on Monday. But
Tuesday, after a harder training, he went to Munich to have a
further examination by his personal physician Dr. Hans-Wilhelm
Mueller-Wohlfarth.
</P>
<P>
"After about an hour and a quarter, he was totally
exhausted," German Davis Cup captain Niki Pilic said. "It's 99
percent sure that he won't play any singles. A five-set match for
him would be too much." 
