<HEADLINE> 13 Injured in Plane Collision at Manila Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- 13 people were injured when a
Philippine Airline (PAL) Boeing 737 and a light aircraft collided
last night on the runway of the Manila domestic airport.
</P>
<P>
According to local media reports today, the PAL plane, bound
for Bacolod city with more than 130 people aboard, was taxiing for
take off at about 7:20 p.m. when it collided with the 18-seat twin
engine aircraft.
</P>
<P>
11 PAL passengers and the pilot and co-pilot of the small plane
were slightly injured and taken to a PAL clinic.
</P>
<P>
Francisco Atayde, airport general manager, said the body of the
small plane, which is owned by the Pacific Airways, was damaged
and its wing was broken. The nose of the PAL aircraft was also
damaged. 
</P>
