<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gansu Becomes China's Main Producer of Rainbow Trout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
has become the largest rainbow trout production base in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that last year the province produced 719 tons
of the fish, accounting for 50 percent of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
The rainbow trout is one of the four most highly prized fish in
the world both for sport and food.
</P>
<P>
Ruan Yashou and Li Qinggui of the Gansu Agricultural Sciences
Institute introduced the fish into the province in 1976 for the
first time.
</P>
<P>
Since then, rainbow trout has been bred on a large scale in
Yongchang and Yongdeng counties.
</P>
<P>
During the past few years experts have done a lot of research
on the breeding of rainbow trout, thus raising the output of the
fish.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1995 the province had about 14.4 ha of lakes and
reservoirs where rainbow trout thrived and the per ha output of
the fish reached 80,000 kg to 150,000 kg.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
