<HEADLINE> Bordeaux Beats Prague 1-0 in UEFA Cup Semi-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Bordeaux of France scored a 1-0
away victory over hosts Slavia Prague in their UEFA Cup semi-final
first leg match here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Striker Christophe Dugarry, who struck twice in Bordeaux's
quarter-final victory over AC Milan, scored the only goal in the
seventh minute from a cross by Zinedine Zidane, who had swept past
defender Radek Bejbl.
</P>
<P>
Dugarry came close to increasing Bordeaux's lead in the first
half, hitting the crossbar once and having several shots saved by
Slavia keeper Jan Stejskal.
</P>
<P>
The Czech squad was dominant in the second half, but failed to
break down a seemingly impenetrable Bordeaux defence.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will meet again for the second leg in Bordeaux in
two weeks time. 
</P>
