<HEADLINE> Barcelona Draw with Bayern in UEFA Cup Semi-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Barcelona surged back to snatch a
2-2 draw with hosts Bayern Munich in the UEFA Cup semi-final first
leg match in Munich on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Trailing 1-2, Romanian Gheorghe Hagi took advantage of a back
pass from Bayern's German international defender Markus Babbel to
fire home the equaliser for Barcelona with his left foot in the
77th minute.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona opened a 1-0 lead only 15 minutes into the first half
after Oscar Garcia played a brilliant one-two with Jose Maria
Bakero through the middle of their defense and hit the ball into
the right-hand corner.
</P>
<P>
But the Bayern, bidding for their first European trophy for 20
years, came out after the interval and went 2-1 ahead with goals
from Marcel Witeczek and Mehmet Scholl in the 52nd and 57th
minutes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
