<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-02 21:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exhumation of Serb Bodies in Mrkonjic Grad Continues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Seventy-eight Serb bodies have
been exhumed from a mass grave discovered at the orthodox cemetery
in te Serb town of Mrkonjic Grad in western Bosnia, the Serb
military prosecution in Banja Luka said today.
</P>
<P>
The bodies were Serbs killed in an offensive launched by joint
Bosnian Croat and Croatian regular army troops in central and
western Bosnia last autumn. Under the Dayton peace accord, these
occupied areas were returned to Serbs on February 4.
</P>
<P>
The exhumation began from an unmarked grave on March 30. The
bodies, mainly those of civilians, had been simply thrown into the
grave, the Tanjug news agency said.
</P>
<P>
One of the bodies was identified as a 74-year-old man who was
beaten to death as there were no injuries caused by firearms on
his body.
</P>
<P>
A full analysis will be conducted on the basis of findings by a
team of experts, led by Zoran Stankovic, pathologist from
Belgrade's military academy hospital.
</P>
<P>
According to Stankovic, injuries on the bodies indicate that
many victims were tortured to death in a brutal manner.
</P>
<P>
The exhumation is expected to end later this week, depending on
weather conditions, Tanjug said.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities in Mrkonjic Grad say that there are several
more mass graves in the area.
</P>
<P>
The exhumation at the orthodox cemetery, where about 200 Serb
civilians and soldiers are believed to have been buried, is being
conducted in the presence of international officials, domestic and
foreign reporters as well as a large number of citizens and the
victims' relatives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960403.0339 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-02 21:34 </DATE_TIME>
