<HEADLINE> Plane With US Commerce Secretary Crashes Over Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The plane carrying U.S. Commerce
Secretary Ron Brown crashed today during a flight from Tuzla in
northeastern Bosnia to the Croatian Adriatic town of Dubrovnik,
reports from Sarajevo said.
</P>
<P>
According to unnamed diplomatic sources in Sarajevo, the plane
crashed off Dubrovnik.
</P>
<P>
International peace Implementation Force (IFOR) spokesman in
Sarajevo Jorst Fohmann also confirmed that a plane had crashed in
the region of Dubrovnik.
</P>
<P>
Brown was on a three-day tour of Bosnia and Croatia, during
which he had visited Tuzla this morning. On this mission, Brown
was accompanied by 12 U.S. businessmen engaged in the areas of
telecommunications, transport, tourism, and infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
